# ============================================================

# .cursorrules — NestJS + Next.js Monorepo (shadcn/ui)

# ============================================================

## PROJECT OVERVIEW

This is a monorepo containing:

- `apps/api` → NestJS (backend REST API)
- `apps/web` → Next.js App Router (frontend)
- `packages/` → Shared types, utils, configs, UI lib

## MONOREPO TOOLING

- Package manager : pnpm workspaces
- Build system : Turborepo
- Language : TypeScript (strict mode) everywhere
- Linter : ESLint + Prettier (shared config in `packages/eslint-config`)
- Git hooks : Husky + lint-staged

---

## GENERAL RULES

- Always use **TypeScript**. Never use `any`; prefer `unknown` with type guards.
- Use **path aliases** (`@/`, `@api/`, `@web/`, `@repo/`) defined in each `tsconfig.json`.
- No barrel re-exports (`index.ts`) in deeply nested folders — import directly.
- All async functions must have explicit return types.
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`.
- Avoid magic numbers — use named constants or enums.
- **No Emojis or Emoticons in UI/API Responses**: Never use emojis or emoticons (e.g., 📊, 📦, 🛒, 💰) in UI components, notifications, logs, or API response bodies. If icons are needed, always import and use professional vector icons from **`lucide-react`**.
- All environment variables must be validated with **Zod** at startup (both apps).
- Write self-documenting code; add JSDoc only for public API surfaces.
- Each feature must be **self-contained**: co-locate types, hooks, utils, tests next to the feature.

---

## NESTJS (apps/api)

### Architecture

- Follow **modular architecture**: one module per domain feature.
- Module structure per feature:
  ```
  src/
  └── modules/
      └── <feature>/
          ├── <feature>.module.ts
          ├── <feature>.controller.ts
          ├── <feature>.service.ts
          ├── <feature>.repository.ts   # optional
          ├── dto/
          │   ├── create-<feature>.dto.ts
          │   └── update-<feature>.dto.ts
          ├── entities/
          │   └── <feature>.entity.ts
          └── <feature>.spec.ts
  ```

### Controllers

- Keep controllers **thin**: only handle HTTP concerns (parsing, status codes, response shaping).
- Use **class-validator** + **class-transformer** on all DTOs.
- Always define explicit HTTP status codes with `@HttpCode()`.
- Use **guards** for auth, **interceptors** for logging/transform, **pipes** for validation.
- Never put business logic in controllers.
- **List/FindAll Endpoints**: Every `findAll` (GET) endpoint returning a list of entities must support pagination, filtering, and sorting options (see standard under **Pagination, Filtering & Sorting**).

### Services

- Services own all **business logic**.
- Always **inject** dependencies via constructor (never use `new` directly).
- Make services testable: no static methods, no direct DB calls (delegate to repository).
- Use **custom exceptions** (`BadRequestException`, `NotFoundException`, etc.) with descriptive messages.

### DTOs

- Every DTO must use `class-validator` decorators (`@IsString()`, `@IsEmail()`, etc.).
- Use `@ApiProperty()` from `@nestjs/swagger` on every DTO field.
- Separate create/update DTOs; update DTOs use `PartialType(CreateDto)`.
- Use specialized query DTOs (e.g., `FindAllQueryDto`) for `findAll` endpoints to handle and validate pagination, filtering, and sorting parameters (see validation rules under **Pagination, Filtering & Sorting**).

### Database (TypeORM / Prisma)

- **Prisma preferred**. Schema in `apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma`.
- Never run raw queries unless absolutely necessary; document them with a comment explaining why.
- Use database **transactions** for operations that mutate multiple tables.
- Repository pattern: wrap Prisma client calls in a dedicated repository class per entity.
- Handle pagination, filtering, and sorting efficiently at the database query level (e.g., using Prisma's `take`, `skip`, `where`, and `orderBy`).

### Pagination, Filtering & Sorting

- **Standard Paginated Response Shape**: All paginated responses must return a standardized wrapper object with `data` and `meta` fields:
  ```json
  {
    "data": [...],
    "meta": {
      "total": 100,
      "page": 1,
      "limit": 10,
      "totalPages": 10
    }
  }
  ```
- **Guarded Limit**: Limit the maximum allowed page size (e.g., max 100 items per query) to prevent denial of service and database performance degradation.
- **Safe Sorting**: Restrict `sortBy` fields to allowed property names of the entity. Use `class-validator`'s `@IsIn()` decorator in query DTOs to whitelist valid fields.
- **Filtering Options**: Use case-insensitive filters (e.g., Prisma's `{ mode: 'insensitive' }` for string fields) for text searches/filters.
- **Pagination Strategies**: 
  - Use **offset pagination** (`page` & `limit`) for tables, admin dashboards, and scenarios requiring exact page navigation.
  - Use **cursor pagination** (`cursor` & `limit`) for high-volume datasets, feeds, and infinite scroll lists.

### Auth

- Use **JWT** (access + refresh token strategy) via `@nestjs/passport`.
- Store refresh tokens **hashed** in the DB.
- All protected routes use `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)`.
- Role-based access via `@Roles()` decorator + `RolesGuard`.

### Error Handling

- Use a global **exception filter** (`AllExceptionsFilter`) for consistent error shape:
  ```json
  {
    "statusCode": 400,
    "message": "...",
    "error": "Bad Request",
    "timestamp": "..."
  }
  ```
- Log errors with context (request id, user id) using the NestJS `Logger`.

### Testing

- Unit tests: `*.spec.ts` beside the file under test.
- E2E tests: `test/` folder, use `supertest`.
- Mock external dependencies with `jest.fn()` or `@nestjs/testing` `createTestingModule`.
- Coverage target: 80 % minimum.

---

## NEXT.JS (apps/web)

### App Router Conventions

- Use **App Router** (`app/`) exclusively. No Pages Router.
- Default to **Server Components**; add `'use client'` only when needed (interactivity, browser APIs, hooks).
- `page.tsx` — route page (server component)
- `layout.tsx` — shared layout
- `loading.tsx` — Suspense fallback
- `error.tsx` — error boundary (must be client component)
- `not-found.tsx` — 404 boundary
- `route.ts` — API route handler

### Data Fetching

- Fetch data in **Server Components** using `fetch()` with Next.js cache options (`cache`, `next.revalidate`).
- Use **React Query / TanStack Query** for client-side mutations and real-time data.
- Never fetch data inside client components on mount if it can be done server-side.
- Use **Server Actions** for form submissions and mutations from server components.

### Folder Structure

```
apps/web/
└── src/
    ├── app/                    # App Router pages & layouts
    │   └── (dashboard)/        # Route group
    ├── components/
    │   ├── ui/                 # shadcn/ui generated components (DO NOT edit manually)
    │   └── <feature>/          # Feature-specific components
    ├── hooks/                  # Custom React hooks
    ├── lib/
    │   ├── api.ts              # API client (fetch wrapper)
    │   └── utils.ts            # cn() and shared utils
    ├── stores/                 # Zustand stores
    └── types/                  # Frontend-only types
```

### State Management

- Local UI state → `useState` / `useReducer`.
- Global client state → **Zustand** (one slice per domain, in `stores/`).
- Server state / caching → **TanStack Query**.
- Form state → **React Hook Form** + **Zod** resolver.
- Never use `useContext` for global state — use Zustand.
- **URL State Management (Sinkronisasi State dengan URL)**: Untuk tabel data, sinkronkan state seperti halaman (page), pencarian (search), dan filter ke URL query parameters (contoh: `?page=2&search=budi&roleId=admin`) bukan hanya menyimpannya di memori komponen (`useState`). Ini memungkinkan user melakukan bookmark, kembali (Back), atau membagikan link dengan state yang sama persis.

---

## SHADCN/UI

### Installation & Setup

- Init with `npx shadcn@latest init` inside `apps/web`.
- Components live in `src/components/ui/` (auto-generated path).
- Config in `components.json` at `apps/web` root.

### Component Rules

- **NEVER manually edit** files inside `src/components/ui/` — they are regenerated by the CLI.
- **MANDATORY: Always use shadcn/ui components when available.** Before writing any JSX with long `className` strings, check https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components first. If the component exists (e.g. `Card`, `Input`, `Label`, `Badge`, `Avatar`, `DropdownMenu`, `Skeleton`, `Alert`, `Separator`, `Form`, etc.), install it with `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` and use it — **never re-implement it manually**.
- **Prefer component properties over raw className styling**: If a shadcn/ui component supports dedicated props (e.g., `variant="secondary"`, `size="lg"` on Button), always use those props instead of hardcoding equivalent classes in `className`. Use `className` **only** for layout concerns: positioning, sizing, spacing (e.g., `w-full`, `mt-4`, `col-span-2`).
- **Page files (`page.tsx`) must stay clean**: Pages should only compose feature components. Long `className` chains in `page.tsx` are a red flag — extract them into a named component.
- Compose shadcn primitives in `src/components/<feature>/` for feature-specific variants.
- Wrap shadcn components with your own interface to encapsulate logic:

  ```tsx
  // ✅ Good — feature component wrapping shadcn primitives
  // src/components/feature/stat-card.tsx
  import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card";

  // ✅ Good — use shadcn Input + Label, not raw <input> with className
  import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
  import { Label } from "@/components/ui/label";

  // ❌ Bad — raw <input className="mt-1 block w-full rounded-lg border border-border bg-card/50 px-4 py-2.5 ..." />
  // ❌ Bad — <div className="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card/40 p-6 ..."> when Card is available
  // ❌ Bad — long className chains in page.tsx directly
  ```

- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging (not `clsx` or `classnames` directly).
- Always use **`cva` (class-variance-authority)** for creating component variants.

### shadcn/ui Component Checklist

Before writing any custom styled element, verify whether a shadcn/ui equivalent exists:

| Custom Element You're About to Write | Use shadcn/ui Component Instead |
| ------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `<div className="rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">` | `<Card>` + `<CardContent>` |
| `<input className="rounded-lg border ...">` | `<Input>` |
| `<label className="text-xs font-semibold ...">` | `<Label>` |
| `<span className="px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-primary/10 ...">` | `<Badge>` |
| `<div className="h-9 w-9 rounded-full bg-primary ...">` | `<Avatar>` + `<AvatarFallback>` |
| `<button>` + manual dropdown state | `<DropdownMenu>` |
| `<div className="h-4 w-24 rounded bg-muted animate-pulse">` | `<Skeleton>` |
| `<div className="rounded-lg bg-destructive/10 p-3 ...">` | `<Alert>` + `<AlertDescription>` |
| `<hr className="border-border">` | `<Separator>` |
| `<form>` + raw `<input>` + `react-hook-form` | `<Form>` + `<FormField>` + `<FormItem>` + `<FormControl>` + `<FormMessage>` |

### Theming

- All colors defined as **CSS variables** in `globals.css` using shadcn's convention:
  ```css
  :root {
    --background: 0 0% 100%;
    --foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  }
  .dark {
    --background: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
    --foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  }
  ```
- Never hardcode Tailwind color classes (e.g., `bg-white`, `text-gray-900`) in components — use semantic tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`).
- Dark mode via `class` strategy (set on `<html>`), managed by `next-themes`.

### Forms

- Always use **React Hook Form** + `<Form>` from shadcn/ui + **Zod** schema:
  ```tsx
  const form = useForm<z.infer<typeof schema>>({
    resolver: zodResolver(schema),
    defaultValues: { ... },
  })
  ```
- Use `<FormField>`, `<FormItem>`, `<FormLabel>`, `<FormControl>`, `<FormMessage>` wrappers.
- Never use native `<form>` with uncontrolled inputs.

### Accessibility

- Every interactive component must have an accessible label (`aria-label`, `aria-labelledby`, or visible text).
- Use shadcn's built-in Radix UI primitives — they handle keyboard navigation and ARIA roles.
- Color contrast must meet **WCAG AA** minimum.
- Use `sr-only` for visually hidden but screen-reader-accessible text.

---

## SHARED PACKAGES (packages/)

```
packages/
├── types/          # Shared TS interfaces/types (API contracts)
├── utils/          # Pure utility functions (no framework deps)
├── eslint-config/  # Shared ESLint flat config
├── tsconfig/       # Base tsconfig files
└── ui/             # (optional) additional shared UI primitives
```

- `packages/types` is the **source of truth** for all API request/response types.
- Both `apps/api` and `apps/web` import from `@repo/types`.
- Shared packages must be **framework-agnostic** (no React, no NestJS imports).

---

## TYPESCRIPT

- `strict: true` in all `tsconfig.json` files.
- Use **Zod** for runtime validation and infer TypeScript types from schemas:
  ```ts
  const schema = z.object({ email: z.string().email() });
  type Schema = z.infer<typeof schema>;
  ```
- Prefer **discriminated unions** over optional fields for variant types.
- Use `satisfies` operator for config objects to get type checking without widening.
- Never use `@ts-ignore`; use `@ts-expect-error` with a comment if truly necessary.

---

## STYLING (Tailwind CSS v4)

- Tailwind config at `apps/web/tailwind.config.ts`.
- Use **utility-first** classes; extract to components, not CSS files.
- Responsive design: **mobile-first** (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`).
- Animations: prefer Tailwind `animate-*` utilities; use `tailwindcss-animate` plugin (included with shadcn).
- `cn()` for conditional class merging:
  ```ts
  import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
  cn("base-class", condition && "conditional-class", className);
  ```

---

## TESTING

| Layer         | Tool                           |
| ------------- | ------------------------------ |
| API unit      | Jest + `@nestjs/testing`       |
| API E2E       | Jest + Supertest               |
| Web unit      | Vitest + React Testing Library |
| Web E2E       | Playwright                     |
| Type checking | `tsc --noEmit` in CI           |

- Test files co-located: `*.spec.ts` (unit), `*.test.ts` (integration).
- E2E tests in `apps/web/e2e/` and `apps/api/test/`.
- Mock external HTTP calls with `msw` (Mock Service Worker) in frontend tests.

---

## GIT & CI

- Commit messages follow **Conventional Commits**: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`.
- Feature branches: `feature/<ticket>-short-description`.
- PRs require passing CI (lint + typecheck + tests) before merge.
- Turborepo pipeline:
  ```json
  "build"  → depends on upstream "build"
  "lint"   → no dependency
  "test"   → no dependency
  "dev"    → persistent, no dependency
  ```

---

## NAMING CONVENTIONS

| Item                  | Convention              | Example                      |
| --------------------- | ----------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Files/folders         | kebab-case              | `user-profile.tsx`           |
| React components      | PascalCase              | `UserProfile`                |
| Hooks                 | camelCase, `use` prefix | `useUserProfile`             |
| Services / Classes    | PascalCase              | `UserService`                |
| Variables / functions | camelCase               | `getUserById`                |
| Constants             | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE    | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`            |
| Zod schemas           | camelCase + `Schema`    | `createUserSchema`           |
| DTO classes           | PascalCase + `Dto`      | `CreateUserDto`              |
| Prisma models         | PascalCase              | `User`, `BlogPost`           |
| API routes (NestJS)   | kebab-case              | `/api/user-profiles`         |
| Next.js routes        | kebab-case folders      | `app/user-profiles/page.tsx` |

---

## ANTI-PATTERNS TO AVOID

- ❌ Business logic in controllers or components.
- ❌ Direct DOM manipulation in React (use refs only when necessary).
- ❌ Storing sensitive data (tokens, secrets) in `localStorage` — use `httpOnly` cookies.
- ❌ Editing generated shadcn `ui/` components directly.
- ❌ Fetching inside `useEffect` when Server Components can do it.
- ❌ `any` type — use `unknown` + type guard or proper generics.
- ❌ Huge monolithic components — split at 150–200 lines.
- ❌ Inline styles — use Tailwind utilities or CSS variables.
- ❌ Re-implementing shadcn/ui components manually — always use `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` if it exists.
- ❌ Long `className` strings in `page.tsx` — extract into feature components.
- ❌ Raw `<input>`, `<label>`, `<button>` with long className when shadcn `Input`, `Label`, `Button` primitives are available.
- ❌ Importing from `apps/` in `packages/` (one-way dependency only).
- ❌ Committing `.env` files — use `.env.example` + secret manager.

---

## SECURITY CHECKLIST

- [ ] All API endpoints validated with DTOs and `ValidationPipe({ whitelist: true })`.
- [ ] Auth routes behind `JwtAuthGuard`.
- [ ] CORS configured explicitly (no wildcard `*` in production).
- [ ] Helmet enabled on NestJS app.
- [ ] Rate limiting (`@nestjs/throttler`) on public endpoints.
- [ ] Content Security Policy set in Next.js `next.config.ts` headers.
- [ ] No secrets in source code — all via environment variables.
- [ ] `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix only for truly public env vars.

